Color Codes for DESCRIPTIONs/attacks and what not<br>
<br>
All colors are pretty self explanatory:<br>
@R -  red<br>
@r -  red<br>
@B -  blue<br>
@b -  blue<br>
@W -  white<br>
@C -  cyan<br>
@c -  cyan<br>
@G -  green<br>
@g -  green<br>
@M -  magenta<br>
@m -  magenta<br>
@Y -  yellow<br>
@y -  yellow<br>
<br>
Lowercase codes are color1 in your color preferences.  Uppercase codes<br>
are color2 in your color preferences.<br>
<br>
Bold Highlight and Underline:<br>
<br>
@e - mild emphasis<br>
@h - highlight<br>
@u - underline<br>
@E - strong emphasis<br>
<br>
Use the colors with emphasis, highlight, and underline (if it works) for<br>
other colors/effects.<br>
<br>
Use @n to return the text to normal.<br>
@I will indent the text as on done this line.<br>
</html>
</body>
